values:
Ok, so I know its been a while since I've updated..but this one isnt gonna be very long bc I just wanna post my school schedule.  If you're @Hayfield, let me know if you have any classes with me!


1. Fashion Marketing 1- Winterbottom
2. Physics 1 Honors- Kinder
3. Precalculus Honors- Engels
4. AP US History- Soled
5. French 4- French
6. Photography 2- Price
7. English 11 Honors- HowardKongolo

Eric: (hold up a picture of me, Megan, and Rikki) What were you doing? Me: I know, I look like I just had sex.....Oh yeah, you were unconscious. Eric: (laughs) Be gentle next time! Becca: Oh yeah.... Becca: Over a foot long... Becca: And really wide. Me: Um...ouch? Becca: lol. Me: ....and how would you walk?

Today was the last full day of school.  From now on, we get out at 11:00 instead of 2:05.  That also means that Ian and Mike will not be driving us because they are seniors and pretty much finished.  I think I'm gonna sk Danny for a ride one day, but seeing how every other time I have asked, he has ahd others in the car and said I couldn't, I;m beginning to think he's avoiding me...boo Danny.  I am happy that its almost summer though...except that tow of my best friends are leaving me. And speaking of that, I found out last night that Katie leaves next Tuesday, not the 5th.  That bites the big one.  I wanted to scream when she told me that.  We're trying to get a sleepover in on saturday....hopefully her parents will say yes, circumstances considered.
 
I actually had fun today...mostly:
English/ History:  We did presentations.  My group was supposed to present on Thursday last week, but the retards couldn't figure out how to make the computer work so we got bumped back to Friday...then the smae thing happened and when they finally did get it working, the groups before us took for-fucking-ever....so we got movd to today.  I told Mrs. Sutton we had to go today because we had already moved twice and we had costumes this time, and she said ok, i'll put you at the top of the list...but did she? NO! she didn't because she is retarded.  AHHHHH!!! I hate that class.  The fucking John Walley was being his annoying self.  he went to get the book and came back with another group's to look at so I asked why he didn't get our and he sarcasticaly told me he couldn't find it.  I really had to hold myself back from slapping him.  Then he looked at me and said "Ya know, you could go get it too....you can."  Like am some lazy ass who had done nothing on the project and forgot to bring my notes on what to say on the presentation...that little bitch must have been looking in a mirror because that pretty much discribes him.  Grrrrrr...I want to punch somebody sooo badly!!!!!  Ok, calming down.  Well, we finally got to present and it pretty much sucked.  Oh well, I did good so those fuckers can get a bad grade for themselves...I'm getting a damn A if i have to kill for it. Whew....on to the next class.
 
Algebra:  This class was basically a waste.  All Mr. J did was collect our grade sheets and talk to students who needed help.  We just sat there and talked the whole time.  I'm gonna miss that class next year because I liked sitting with Shannen and Danny and Kathy...and Mr. Johnson was cool.  I showed Danny my portfolio and he said he might take photgraphy next year.  Too bad he's gonna be at the new school and I'm not.  Then Shanned told us some of her bad girl stories which made me looking like a damn angel.  She says I have a halo.  Lol...oh well, if I feel like changing, i guess I will.
 
Lunch:  Oh yeah, somebody found Erin's history book this morning and gave it to her, right after she went to the finance office and paid for it.  Lol, so I went with her before lunch to get her money back and told her she should just keep the 60 dollars for herself bc her parents think she still paid for it.  I doubt she will though.  Lunch was just Lunch...nough said.
 
French:  Oh my...that was an interesting class.  Me and Becca had some deep conversations.  That thing as 10 fricken pages long.  Tamar saw us writing and was like "Geez, you're writing an essay."  Two guesses what we talked about....lol.  I love her.  She's my sexy bitch.  Take me to the beach with you, sexy bitch. I promise I'll be cool with the boys,...minimal staring.  You, don't even know if they're hot, so whats there to worry about?  Teehee.  Alright, I guess I'll just leave you alone about it and see what happens.  Madame Remaili did nothing that class.  Final is next class.  Fuck.
 
~~Becca: What are you and Tamar doing?  You look like those asian nail polish ladies.~~
 
Photography: Always a pleasure.  Again, nothing to do because it was almost the last class and we just handed in our portfolios.  McKinzie, Amanda, Megan, Rikki, and I all discussed our boy issues.  I have no boys, therefore was mostly just listening and givng input.  Oh yeah, Phillip knows that I'm Stacy now...so we'll see what happens with that.  I will laugh if he calls....because it will be funny.  Mr. Price says we're just gonna watch a movie next class.  I could just not go but I probably will to hang out with Megan for the last time in Photo class...this year at least.
 
There was my day...
 
Ok, now, about boys....my favorite topic.  I feel bad about something.  there is this guy that liked me a while ago and I don't like him in that way at all...he's kinda wierd.  Buuuuuut, I like to be liked and kinda want to be nice so that he'll still like me?  Is that bad?  Haha...yes.  Damn.  Well, at least I admit it.  Other than that little epiphony I had of liking the fact that he liked me, nothing with boys has really changed....blah!!!!!  We also debated whether or not we like the idea of a boyfriend better than the boyfriends himself when we get one.  I found that to be true in some circumstances.
 
 
 
I could flirt with all the guys
Smile at the them and bat my eyes
Press against them when we dance
Make then think they stand a chance
Then refuse to see it through
That's a thing I'd never do
 
I could stay home every night
Wait around for mister right
Take cold showers every day
And just throw my life away
On a dream that won't come true
Thats a thing I'd never do
 
I could hurt some one like me
Out of spite or jelousy
I don't steal and I don't lie
But I can feel and I can cry
A fact I bet you never knew
Cuz to cry in front of you....
...that's the worst thing I could do.

Becca = Whore.  Way to effing bitch about me for like, half an entry.  Lol, you love me, i know it...bc you just keep comin back for more!!!  I liked you shirt by the way.  Ok so, its late, im tired, im going to sleep.

Ok, so I think I should update because I haven't in really long time.  So, what has been going on with me? 

Well, first off we have this decades project in English and Erin is not in my group with sucks.  Also, I have kept putting off all ogf my work, partially because I don't understand how we're suposed to, like, phrase the summary and partially because I am just lazy.  Lol...probably more the second one.  Ooo, which reminds me..I never got that picture off of Erin's camera so I hope she still has it or else I will have to make something up.

Nothing more school related is happening that is making me stressed really.  Except that there are only 10 days left! Which is great in a way and bad in a way.  Not gonne get into that right now tho.

So it has been really really effing hot for a week or two and yesterday Thomas invited me to his pool for a little party that his neighborhood was having.  So Erin couldn't go but I still went because I didn't think it was wierd.  Is that wierd that I go over to his house when Erin isn't there?  Hmmm....I think my parents think it is a little.  Oh well.  It was fun.  The food was really good and then I got to go swimming for the first time in forever.  Now here's the funny part.  I didn't bring underwear with me to change into and I just wore my bathing suit under my skirt because I didn't actually think we would swim.  So, then we went back to his house for a couple hours till my mom picked me up and I had to borrow a pair of his sister's boxers.  But, then I couldn't wear my skirt over them, so I wore a pair of Thomas's shorts....ok, now, Thomas is really tall and I'm not, so his shorts were like 2 inches below my knees.  It was hilarious man, hilarious.  Then my mom came to pick me up and i was wearing them and she didn't even notice.  That was wierd.  We watched Grease and talked to erin a lot.  Her parents had said that if my mom would bring me over after I was done at his house, i could have spent the night there....but my mommy said no :(  Next week.

Hmmm...what else? Oh yeah, we got our yearbooks on friday and mine is missing like 10 pages out of the seniors but its after my brother's picture so its all good.  As somebody (i think it was Megan) said...more signing space!

Well, I really should shower...then do that damn project so I think I will.

Its getting a little annoying writing in this because I want to, but I dont want to at the same time.  Some random movie is on the TV right now and there is this quite hott guy without a shirt on. mmmmmmm....That made me happy...because like, 90% of my brain is focused on boys 24/7.  I really need to try and give a little more of that to school work. Whatevs.  

So last night I went to Mandy's party and I thoguth Megan was going but then I called her, like 15 minutes before it started and she didn't know about it so....that sucked.  I only knew Laura and Mandy there and they all knew eachother and I just feel awkward in those situations so for the first couple hours, I felt wierd about it.  But then I settled ina nd Thomas showed up, having seen that I was there on my away message, and that as fun. 

I am pretty damn tired right now.  Erin kept me up till 1 last night.  Its aight though...I'm a teenager, its what I do.  I am also home alone because my entire family (including Ian) is working.  It's actually kinda nice to be home alone.  I would rather be out with a friend, but its aight.  Oh, yeah, Happy birthday Mrs. McKenna.  

So...I'm gonna go do something productive.

Oh, and, Erin, watch out if we're still in sync bc I found out why I have been hating the world for the past few days....lol.

Have you ever had that feeling when you were hanging around your friends and they're talking, not even to you, just, like, talking and it pisses you off to the point where you think "Wow, just shut up!"?  Well, I have felt that way all fricken day.  Today sucked.  I don't know why.  Maybe I'm sleep deprived from staying up an extra hour last night. Ok, here goes....

This morning, we got in the car and of course Ian cannot stand driving when other cars are present and bitched at me for being a minute late to the car because in those 60 seconds, all of the cars around him that were forcing him to only go 5 mph over the speed limit magically appeared.  ugh....jerk.

So then I got to school and we went to the Media Center for English/ History class and had to do fucking research on Decades.  I had to spend money to copy, like, 50 pages out of some book for information because we must have photocopies of all our sources go into "the book".  I hate Mrs. Sutton.  Mmmk, moving on.  I felt like passing out the whole time during that class and one of the guys in my group is really really annoying so that just made it worse.

Ok, then came Math...that was ok.  I got candy because my column was making the best progress on that stupid final review packet.  I had to ask Danny for help so many times though.  And then everybody in the class had to also.  Somebody was like "I don't get it." and he said sarcastically "Of course you don't.....". I thought that was really funny because they never ever ssem to understand the easiest stuff in that class.  But i guess I shouldn't talk because I have asked for help many a time as well.

Ok, so Health was next and the klids in that class never shut their mouths either.  They just talk and atalk and talk until the teacher gets pissed...then they wait five seconds and start talking again.  Today, being in my PMS-y mood (even though its not time for that yet), it was really bugging me so by the end of that class, I was ready to kill somebody...ahhhhh.

Lunch- Fine.  Megan's boyfriend,  Bryan came over and talked to me.  He's nice.  He went to tap my shoulder when he was leaving and I flinched....like really flinched and he looked all surprised and was like "did you think I was gonna hit you?"  Sitting at that table has made me paranoid. lol. 

Chemistry sucked.  I hate it.  I never want to go to it again.  AHHHHH....
OK, we had to do this stupid titration lab and at frist I was the only fucking person actually trying to do the work in my group (at least it seemed that way....thomas was helping though) then I was doing it and I messed up the first one and made it really pink which is bad so i felt alright because that was what was suposed to happen.  Then, for the second trial, i forgot to put the indicator in it so it didnt work at all and we wasted the chemicals and had to start over so i felt like and idiot.  So then, when we were doing it over, i was putting the base in and it got incredibly pink again!  So they were, like, bitching at me.  I just put down the stuff, walked to the other side of the lab bench and said "somebody else fucking do it them" (thats exaggerated actually).  So Chris decided to do it.  He is so wierd.  I was on his list and now he, like, calls me hot and pretty and makes kissy faces at me whenever he sees me.  And OH YEAH! He told a fucking nazi and rascist joke.  I wanted to punch him in the face!  So then we did the last two trials and added MORE base than I had put in, so I was doing it alright, we just hadn't let it sit long enough.  Then wehn I said something like that, Thomas said "We know, nobody said you did anything wrong..." then got quieter and said "...just stop whining about it."  So I shut up and let them do it, cleaned up, and sat down.  Then, Mrs. Engles passed back our unit tests and I had gotten an 87.5 out of 11 which i knew wasn't good so I was upset (later she told us that the ones who finished EK early got 10 points added to that so I really had a B+) and when Thomas asked me what I got, I said i didn't want to tell.  Then, when we passed them forward, he went through them and saw what I got and, like, bitched at me for being upset about it, which made me more irritated than what had been building up all day....but I understand that he wasn't in a good mood either, so whatever.

Wow, this is getting long and I'm not done yet.  

After school, I went straight to my locker because I was pissed and then met Erin @thomas's locker and we came here, to her house on the bus.  That was actually fun and now I am in a much better mood, but I am still really fricken tired.

Ok, so now I guess I can be finished.  Maybe I'll write again later....

So....
Erin is here.  That is really cool.  I like having a friend here all the time because I get bored very easily and now I have my best friend right here whenever I need to talk to her! Yay!  We have taken at least 100 pictures of ourselves because, yes, she does that too.  lol.
 
There isn't really much to write right now....but I'll update later.

It is almost 8:00 and I don't know why I am not still asleep.  I want to be, but its just not working so I got out of bed.  Lastnight, at like, 10:00 I passed out.  I wasn't even tired.  I was just lying in my bedd awaiting a return message from Thomas or Erin (which never came, by the way....bitches) and then it was, like 7:00 in the morning and I woke up.  It must have been those cleaning chemicals.  That was....whew...it smelled soooo bad and was still there like an hour after I had cleaned the shower.  I probably should have done the shower last so I wouldn't be smelling it while I cleaned the rest of the bathroom.  Oh well, now my bathroom is fairly spotless as is my bedroom.  There is no junk on the floor! Nothing that I don't plan to be there!.  However, my desk is cluttered still.
 
Me and my mom are goin to pick ERIN up at 9:00 to bring her here where she will be kept until......forever!  No, just till Thursday. 
 
There was a place by Thomas's house for sale and my mom wanted to look at because she wants to move closer to school.  That would be awsome beyond belief to live there because Thomas is like, two houses down and Becca is down teh street.  Buuuuuuut....I have become accustomed to my rather large bedroom and where I live.  It would be wierd.  I love my room and my house and my neighborhood....well, the neighborhood is good, but it would be a lot better to be right next to one of my best friends.  I doubt that we are gonna move though.  My parents have been saying that since I was at Browne. 
 
Ok, I'm gonna go find something productive to do...like make my bed...or wash my face because i feel gross.

Mmmm...I smell like i just came from the beach.  I didn't though.  Today, Thomas had to go to his pool all day to pass out pool passes to the neighborhood people.  So, he invited me and Erin to come over and hang out with him but she couldn't come so it was just us two.  We stayed at the pool for a good three hours and I got a nice tan.  We sat on the lounge chairs and he had to tell two people that were "delinquent" hat they couldn't have passes.  I like sitting by the pool.  Its realaxing.  And i got some color.
 
Then it started to rain and thunder so we went back to his house to watch TV but his parents weren't there so instead we had some crazy sex.....wow, just kidding.  We did watch TV...some sport relay race where football players competed on ESPN.  Then we got pizza from Stone Hot and I ate tooo much.  I had, like, four slices. Lol, I felt like a pig.  I really like his dog, Cookie.  She's a dalmation and i remmeber that wehn I was little, I always wanted a dalmation puppy but my mom would say we couldn't get one and explain to me that they grow out of being puppies. Oooook, so after watching TV, we went back to the pool because his mom called and told him too.  It was ok though because it was starting to get sunny again, even though I had to wear my sweater and he used my towel as a blanket (got a funny picture of that, but you probably had to be there to appreciate the humor....lol).  Nobody else came to the pool for passes.  It was just us, the lifeguard and the supervisor who's skirt was toooooo short.  Then his mom got there and my dad came to pick me up.
 
That was my day.  I had a lot of fun.  Thomas is funny...lol.  It would have been cooler if Erin could have come...butthead.  Lol, just kidding,....I love you!
 
So now I have been trying soooo hard to get my room clean for tomorrow morning when my little birdie comes to stay with me, but somehow it never quite gets clean.  I dusted yesterday, but that just seemed to make it look dirtier.  WTF?  Ughhh....I guess I'll try again later.  I still have to do the bathroom too. Ahhhh!!!  Erin, I am really glad that you are coming tomorrow, but do I really need to cleean for you?  yes, yes I do.
 
Hmm....what else is there to talk about?  Took the Chemistry final yesterday.  That was a bitch.  Kathy and I were, like sharing answers but didn't know the same ones so that probably didn't help much.  At least I get ten extra points added for finishing my EK early.
 
Yesterday after school...What did I do?  Did I do anything?  I can't fucking remember....somebody tell me if you know.  Oh wait!  I know. Mike came over and we watched Aviator and ate chinese food.  "Way of the future, way of the future, way of the future....".  That guy was caaaarazy.
 
So tomorrow....ERIN FREAKING DURIAN IS COMING OVER!!!!!!  Then, Thomas said he wanted to come over, but thats lookin pretty iffy.  My dad wants to go to the Memorial Day Parade so maybe Erin will come over and we'll hang out here alone.  Then Monday, we will be at Springfield Mall.
 
I wa sooo wired last night.  I have no idea why.  But i was dusting at, like, 11:00 and talking on teh phone with Megan and she was like "Wow, I have never heard you talk this fast."  I am a true night person.  In the morning....no....but at night...lets party!  By the way, Megan is quite the lucky little bitch this week.  Love you dearest!
 
Ok my loves, i should end this intry because it is getting really long.
 
PS.  Dad finally got the top down on the Jeep.
 
 
 
I'm a bitch,
I'm a tease,
I'm a goddess
On my knees
When you hurt
When you suffer
I'm your angel undercover
 
I'm your hell
I'm your dream
I'm nothing inbetween
You know you wouldn't want it any other way...

Ok, I havent really done a good update in a few days, so here goes.
 
Megan has a boyfriend now and I am soo excited for her.  He's nice too.  He even came to my lunch table today and talked to me for a while..and it wasn't awkward.  Thomas doesn't even do that. May be he should be my new best guy friend....lol, j/k.  I love you Thomas and until he writes my name on dessert for me, you will still be my favorite boyfriend in "the group".  Anyways, I approve Megan (like you care..lol.)
 
Also, they were selling those matchmaker thingys at lunch today that they were supposed to sell before valentine's day.  A little late, but I still wanted it.  Apparently, there is an 87.5% chance that PT would like me.  Oy vey.  There is also an 83.2% percent chance that I would like naked man in the garage (aka Erin's brother). 
 
Nothing else is really new.  I am finally done with SOLS as of today.  Last one was this morning.  Now I just have to make it through finals in the coming month and I will be free!  Summer, here I come!
 
Next week is gonna be so fucking good.  I just want this one to end so I can get right into the three day week.  Monday then Friday then Monday off again!  Also, Erin will be sleeping at my house Sunday through Thursay...thats right....5 days!  So here is how my weekend is looking.... Saturday: Thomas's pool for something....Sunday: Erin!....Monday: Mall, or maybe not seeing how my friends are psycho....shhhh! We'll talk about it later...lol...
 
What else?  Oh yeah...no, he has not called me.  I'm not counting on it, but just wanted to let whoever reads this know.  Now Thomas is targetting somebody else to hook my up with. Gotta love my friends.
 
I'm gonna end this now....I'll add more if I think of something.
 
 
 
Its me and the moon she says
And I've got no trouble with that
And I am a butterfly But you wouldn't let me die....
 
You marry a role and you give up your soul 'til you break down.

You Know You're From Northern Virginia If... 
1. Speed limits are just suggestions 
2. You take a major highway to school (95, 66,28, etc) 
3. You constantly complain about there being nothing to do, even though you are right next to D.C.
4. You have at least 2 friends who have no idea what their parents do because its "top secret" government work 
5. 50% of your senior class plans on going either to Mason, JMU, Tech or UVA , 
6. When people ask where you're from, you tell them DC because its easier to explain 
7. You've never told someone you're from Virginia without putting "northern" in front of it 
8. When you and your friends get bored you all whip out your cell phones and start playing with them 
9. Its not actually tailgating unless your bumper is touching the car in front of you.
10. A yellow light means at least 5 more cars can get through. 
11. A red light means 2 more can. 
12. It takes you 30 minutes to drive 10 miles
13. Your local news is national news 
14. If you hear the word "! sniper" one more time you're going to slap someone 
15. You actually know what the black boxes at stoplights are for 
16. Even if your high school is only a year old, its already overcrowded 
17. You >will< have over 500 students in your graduating class 
18. Despite the fact that Virginia fought for the south in the Civil War, you are NOT, under ANY circumstances, a "southerner" 
19. You are friends with people from at least 2 other high schools 
20. You know at least 2 people who drive a Mercedes, BMW, Lexus, etc.
21. The cars in the student parking lot are worth 3x those in the teacher parking lot. 
22. You are amused by visiting relatives who are actually excited to see Washington DC 
23. You are amazed when you go out of town and the people at McDonalds speak English 
24. You can cross 4 lanes of traffic in under 30 seconds 
25. There are at least 3 malls within 20 minutes of your house

Body: This was written by a guy who has years of experience. Believe you me, most of them are true about girls....

1. Whatever you do, don't just show up at herr house...she runs around in their underwear just like we do.

2. DON'T CHEAT ON HER. It may seem foolproof, but girls tell each other everything about everything. Trust me, she WILL find out and you will be mud.

3. Beware of every single male relative and all guy friends. Any of them would kick your ass at the drop of a hat, and a lot of them wouldn't even wait for the damn hat.

4. Never miss an opportunity to tell her she's beautiful.

5. Don't refuse to kiss her in front of your friends. If they laugh at you, it's just because they're jealous.

6. If she slaps you hard, you deserved it.

7. Don't be afraid to touch her if you want to. If she's going out with you in the first place, it's because she likes being in your arms.

8. If you don't sleep with her, DON'T tell your friends that you did.

8.5 If you DO sleep with her, DON'T tell your friends that you did.

9. You can be dirty minded in private, really...most of them are not offended by it...

10. Not all of them eat like birds, a lot of them can eat like whales.

11. Most of them don't mind paying half of everything, but they do discuss these things with their friends. Realize that if you make your girlfriend pay half all the time, everyone will know about it and your friends will know you're a pussy..

11.5 Do you honestly need all your money that much? Be a man, pay all the time!

12. Every girl should eventually get three things from her boyfriend- a stuffed animal, one of his sweatshirts, and a really pretty ring. Even if it's not a serious relationship.

13. Make sure she gets home safely as often as you can. If you're dropping her off, walk her to the door. If you aren't dropping her off, call to be sure she's home safely.

14. If a guy is bothering her, it is your right to beat the shit out of him.

15. If you're talking to a female friend of yours, pull your girlfriend closer.

16. Never, EVER slap her, even if it's just in a joking way. Even if she swats you first, and says, "Oh, you're so dumb" or something, never make any gestures back.

17. Go to a chick flick once in a while. She doesn't care whether you enjoy it or not, it just matters that you went.

18. You're dead meat if you can't get along with their pets, parents, and best friends. Be prince charming to their friends, Mr. Polite to their parents, and make sure to be nice to their animals.

19. Don't flirt with their moms...that's just freaky.

20. Don't be freaked out by PMS. It's not gross, and it really does make them feel like shit, so be understanding.

21. If you don't like the way they drive, you do it.

22. If you're officially dating, and you're introducing her to your friends, you'd better damn well introduce her as your girlfriend.

23. Don't stress where you go for every date. They really only want to be with you.

24. If they complain that something hurts, rub it for them without being asked.

25. Girls are fragile. Even if you're play fighting/wrestling, be very gentle.

26. Memorize their god damn birthdays. You forget her birthday and you're basically screwed for life.

27. Don't marinade the cologne, but smell good.

28. Don't give her something stupid for her birthday or Christmas or Valentine's day. It doesn't have to be expensive, but it has to be meaningful. Jewelry is always nice.

29. If you think the relationship isn't going to last, don't wait to find out. It will only hurt you more if you draw it out.

30. After you've been dating for a while, realize that they really have started to trust you. When you have a girlfriend who truly trusts you, you have a lot more responsibility, privilege and control than you would think. Be careful with it, most guys would kill for that kind of power, and it can be lost in a nanosecond.

(If you have read this and you are a girl, then some of these things are actually really true...am I right?! And if you read this and you are a guy, then these are like the mother fuckin best tips you could ever get!)
